<div><div><h2>Lead futures slide 0.42% on low demand</h2></div><div>"lead prices fell by 0.42 per cent to rs 143.20 per kg in futures trade monday after speculators reduced their exposure amid a weak trend at the spot market due to subdued demand.at the multi commodity exchange lead for delivery in november was down by 60 paise of 0.42 per cent to trade at rs 143.20 per kg in business turnover of 653 lots.marketmen said off-loading of bets by participants owing to slackened demand from consuming industries particularly battery-makers at the physical markets mainly weighed on lead prices at futures trade."</div></div>